.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-env-hibernate - Hibernate an environment (saves to blob storage, frees pool slot)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock env hibernate  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Save the environment state to blob storage and free its pool VM. The
environment transitions from 'running' to 'hibernated'. While hibernated, only
the base-fee is billed (no active-rate charges).

.PP
Use 'bcdock env resume' to bring it back. Use --wait to block until hibernation
completes instead of returning immediately.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  4   rate-limited
  5   environment not found
  10  hibernation failed


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for hibernate

.PP
\fB--wait\fP[=false]
	Block until hibernated or failed

.PP
\fB--wait-timeout\fP=0s
	Max time to wait (default: 10m)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock env hibernate my-env
  bcdock env hibernate my-env --wait
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-env(1)\fP
